===Phonosemantic interpretation===

[[w:Old_Chinese|Old Chinese]] [[w:Old_Chinese_phonology#Initials|Initial]] {{IPAchar|/*s-/}} lends semantic value '''Small/Thin/Slender'''. ([[w:Old_Chinese_phonology#Vowels|Vowel]] {{IPAchar|/*-o-/}} lends semantic value '''Curvature''' or '''Curve and surround/envelop'''.)
Two distinct [[w:Chinese_characters#Pictograms|pictograms]], one depicting a small child and the other a child with rapidly growing hair, were merged into 子. Conceptually, a child was understood as one of a figurative pile of offspring. The ancient readings of the characters were *sag and *sog, respectively.
