=====Usage notes=====
In some kanji compounds, {{Jpan|子}} is part of the word but does not carry much meaning in Japanese, as in {{term|lang=ja|椅子|tr=isu||chair}}.  Possibly because of this erosion of meaning, spelling out {{Jpan|子}} in some compounds has become optional, as in {{term|lang=ja|椰子}} vs. {{term|lang=ja|椰|tr=yashi||a palm tree}}, or {{term|lang=ja|柚子}} vs. {{term|lang=ja|柚|tr=yuzu||an aromatic citron}}.

Also note that, in some compounds, the ''shi'' or ''su'' reading becomes voiced as ''ji'' or ''zu'' due to [[Appendix:Japanese_glossary#rendaku|rendaku]].

